{
  "message": "fuzz: expand btrfs devitem seed corpus with 12 structured seeds\n\nAdd 12 structured corpus seeds for fuzz_btrfs_devitem covering:\n\nValid cases:\n- valid_minimal_1gb: 1GB device, 4K alignment, no usage\n- valid_large_1tb_half_used: 1TB device, 50% utilization\n- valid_sector_512: 500GB HDD with 512-byte sectors\n- valid_nvme_alignment: NVMe device with 16K alignment\n- valid_device_id_2: Multi-device config (devid=2)\n- valid_high_devid: Maximum u64 device ID\n- valid_full_device: bytes_used equals total_bytes\n- valid_with_uuids: Non-zero UUID and FSID fields\n\nInvalid cases (should be rejected by parser):\n- invalid_zero_devid: devid=0 (must be non-zero)\n- invalid_zero_total_bytes: total_bytes=0 (must be non-zero)\n- invalid_bytes_used_exceeds_total: bytes_used > total_bytes\n\nBoundary cases:\n- truncated_50_bytes: 50 bytes (less than required 98)\n\nPrevious corpus had only 2 seeds (empty + single byte). These\nstructured seeds exercise the validation branches added in recent\ncommits (bd-49x6p, bd-wi399) and provide better coverage for\ndevice geometry edge cases.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
